            <section class="intro">
                <h2>The Website's Goal</h2>
                <p>
                    In an era where digital connectivity shapes societal
                    interactions, youth engagement in governance remains a
                    challenge due to limited access to information, bureaucratic
                    complexities, and a lack of direct communication channels
                    with decision-makers.
                </p>
                <p>
                    <strong>SKonnect: Bridging Youth and Governance</strong> is
                    an information system designed to enhance transparency,
                    accountability, and participation within the Sangguniang
                    Kabataan (SK). By integrating digital platforms, interactive
                    dialogue mechanisms, and data-driven insights, SKonnect
                    fosters meaningful connections between youth and governance
                    structures.
                </p>
                <p>
                    The system aims to modernize SK operations by streamlining
                    digital record-keeping, financial tracking, project
                    monitoring, and public interaction—ultimately contributing
                    to improved governance efficiency and youth participation.
                </p>
            </section>

